.TH "CHAOS" 7 "February 2026" "atomdns handlers" "atomdns authors"

.SH "NAME"
.PP
\fIchaos\fP \- respond to TXT queries in the CH class

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
This is useful for retrieving version or author information from the server by querying a TXT record
for a special domain name in the CH class.

.SH "SYNTAX"
.PP
.RS

.nf
chaos [VERSION] {
    authors {
        "First Author"
        "Second Author"
        ...
    }
}

.fi
.RE

.IP \(bu 4
\fBVERSION\fP is the version to return. Defaults to "Served by atomdns, https://atomdns.miek.nl" if not set.
.IP \(bu 4
The \fB\fCauthors\fR section holds the authors that are returned.


.PP
Note that you have to make sure that this handler will get actual queries for
the following zone \fIprefixes\fP: \fB\fCversion.\fR, \fB\fCauthors.\fR, \fB\fChostname.\fR and \fB\fCid.\fR,
i.e. having \fB\fCversion.example.org\fR will suffice to get queries for the
\fB\fCversion.\fR prefix.

.SH "EXAMPLES"
.PP
Specify all the zones:

.PP
.RS

.nf
version.bind version.server authors.bind hostname.bind id.server authors.server {
    chaos atomdns\-001 {
        authors {
            info@example.org
        }
    }
}

.fi
.RE

.PP
And test with \fB\fCdig\fR:

.PP
.RS

.nf
% dig @localhost CH TXT version.bind

;; ANSWER SECTION:
version.bind.        0    CH    TXT    "atomdns\-001"

.fi
.RE
